Sleeping on a thought, a worry, problem, etc. and thinking about it with a "fresh mind" in the following morning's clarity simply means using your Sympathetic Nervous System (good, activated at sunrise) instead of your Parasympathetic Nervous System (bad, activated at nightfall).

This morning I was "snoozing" in bed in a liminal state between wakefulness and sleep when my alarm rang and fully woke me and I experienced a nameless emotion I had never felt before and the only way I could explain it was "contrast between seriousness and a lack of seriousness"

I was aware that the dream I was half-dreaming was not noteworthy or important and also aware that I had nothing important to do today so the alarm was "impotent" to scare me, but also that both the dream could have been important and the alarm could have been important.

This was experienced as a singular feeling, an emotion I had never felt ever before and has no proper name. It entirely consisted in perceived degrees of seriousness and levity between two states' potentialities. The only way I can describe it is "stygian blue" impossible colors.

Often times you see people give a word to a feeling everyone knows or a new definition/grouping, e.g. redditor "Sonder" for awareness of others, but this was not a new name or definition for a known feeling, but something completely alien, "levity" comes closest, but far from it.
